data.text:
This chart shows The Age of Current World Leaders by country.

Age is the amount of time during which a person or animal has lived.Age is the amount of time during which a thing has existed.Age is the time of life when a person does something or becomes legally able to do something.

The head of the government and the date of birth was also mentioned here. All of the state leaders who have reigned for over 50 years have been monarchs, with the exception of Fidel Castro, who was effectively, though not officially, leader of Cuba for 52 years, 93 days.
